itemDescription: British aristocrat and World War II intelligence agent

wikipedia_page.main: Diana Ruth Wellesley, Duchess of Wellington,  (née McConnel; 14 January 1922 – 1 November 2010) was the wife of Valerian Wellesley, 8th Duke of Wellington, and a British intelligence officer during World War II.

*Diana Wellesley, Duchess of Wellington, 88, British aristocrat and intelligence officer.
